fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
By the universal property of products and coproducts, a map from the coproduct of some objects X_i to their product is given by a matrix of morphisms f_{ij} : X_i \to  X_j. We choose the identity matrix
    f_{ij} = \begin {cases}       \textrm {id} & (i = j) \\       0 & (i \ne  j)     \end {cases}
    where 0 is the additive neutral element in the abelian group \hom (X_i, X_j). This gives a canonical map \coprod _i X_i \to  \prod _i X_i.
